<p><strong>INSTRUCTIONS:</strong> Choose&nbsp;units&nbsp;and enter the foll=
owing:</p>=20
<ul>=20
 <li><strong>(s)</strong>&nbsp;Length of Nonagon Sides</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p><strong>Nonagon Area&nbsp;(A):&nbsp;</strong>The area is returned in squ=
are meters. However, this&nbsp;can be automatically converted to compatible=
&nbsp;units via the pull-down menu.</p>=20
<h3><span>The Math / Science</span></h3>=20
<p>A regular nonagon has nine equal sides and equal angles. The formula for=
 the area of a nonagon is:</p>=20
<p style=3D"margin-left:40px">A =3D9/4=E2=80=A2cot(=CF=80/9)=E2=80=A2s<sup>=
2</sup></p>=20
<p>where:</p>=20
<ul>=20
 <li>A =3D area of a regular nonagon</li>=20
 <li>s =3D length of a side</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p><a href=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/wikiclip/?uuid=3D11cd1475-e2ac-11ed-8f0=
9-bc764e203090" style=3D"float:right;"><img src=3D"https://www.vcalc.com/st=
atic/images/large-wikiclip.png" style=3D"width: 54px; height: 52px;"></a><!=
